604. Calculate the area bounded by the following lines:

1). the parabola $4 y=8 x-x^{2}$ and the line $4 y=x+6$;

2) the parabolas $y=4-x^{2}$ and $y=x^{2}-2 x$;
3) the cubic parabolas $6 x=y^{3}-16 y$ and $24 x=y^{3}-16 y$;
4) the ellipse $x=a \cos t, y=a \sin t$;
5) the cardioid $\rho=a(1+\cos \varphi)$;
6) the circles $\rho=2 \sqrt{3} a \cos \varphi$ and $\rho=2 a \sin \varphi$.

